{"data": {"repository": {"pullRequest": {"id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0MzY5NzM5Mzgz", "number": 1298, "reviewThreads": {"totalCount": 1, "pageInfo": {"startCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMC0wMi0wNFQwMjoxNDo1OFrODc1m1A==", "endCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMC0wMi0wNFQwMjoxNDo1OFrODc1m1A==", "hasNextPage": false, "hasPreviousPage": false}, "nodes": [{"id": "MDIzOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3VGhyZWFkMjMxNTY1MDEyOnYy", "diffSide": "RIGHT", "path": "pom.xml", "isResolved": false, "comments": {"totalCount": 4, "pageInfo": {"startCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMC0wMi0wNFQwMjoxNDo1OFrOFlGLeA==", "endCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMC0wMi0wNVQyMjoyNjo0OVrOFmJWXw==", "hasNextPage": false, "hasPreviousPage": false}, "nodes": [{"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDM3NDQ0Mjg3Mg==", "bodyText": "@prashantwason this has a side effect of making the builds run slower. The reason is that when a build is submitted in travis, it needs to wait for resources to be available for the build to get triggered. My understanding is that if we ask for a larger JVM for non-IntegrationTest modules as well, this will make the process slower.\nHow much more memory is required for the coverage report ?", "url": "https://github.com/apache/hudi/pull/1298#discussion_r374442872", "createdAt": "2020-02-04T02:14:58Z", "author": {"login": "n3nash"}, "path": "pom.xml", "diffHunk": "@@ -113,6 +113,7 @@\n     <spark.bundle.hive.shade.prefix></spark.bundle.hive.shade.prefix>\n     <utilities.bundle.hive.scope>provided</utilities.bundle.hive.scope>\n     <utilities.bundle.hive.shade.prefix></utilities.bundle.hive.shade.prefix>\n+    <argLine>-Xmx1024m -XX:MaxPermSize=256m</argLine>", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": null, "originalCommit": {"oid": "2f304675c0c3b6acbe2a1f8b0e6003f93f7eb203"}, "originalPosition": 4}, {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDM3NDUzNjMxMw==", "bodyText": "I don't think travis has the smarts to grok this and get the resource needs?  We just get a VM with some fixed RAM https://docs.travis-ci.com/user/reference/overview/\n-Xmx won't also grab the 1GB right off the bat.. do you see the builds slowing down? would be interesting to understand why..", "url": "https://github.com/apache/hudi/pull/1298#discussion_r374536313", "createdAt": "2020-02-04T08:42:26Z", "author": {"login": "vinothchandar"}, "path": "pom.xml", "diffHunk": "@@ -113,6 +113,7 @@\n     <spark.bundle.hive.shade.prefix></spark.bundle.hive.shade.prefix>\n     <utilities.bundle.hive.scope>provided</utilities.bundle.hive.scope>\n     <utilities.bundle.hive.shade.prefix></utilities.bundle.hive.shade.prefix>\n+    <argLine>-Xmx1024m -XX:MaxPermSize=256m</argLine>", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDM3NDQ0Mjg3Mg=="}, "originalCommit": {"oid": "2f304675c0c3b6acbe2a1f8b0e6003f93f7eb203"}, "originalPosition": 4}, {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDM3NDkxMzY3Nw==", "bodyText": "I did not add this line. It was already part of the maven-surefire plugin's argLine.  I just moved the definition to a property so that jacoco plugin can add its own java-agent config to it and the unit tests can execute with jacococ agent enabled.\nThis was added in the following commit 3 months ago:\n#979", "url": "https://github.com/apache/hudi/pull/1298#discussion_r374913677", "createdAt": "2020-02-04T20:47:34Z", "author": {"login": "prashantwason"}, "path": "pom.xml", "diffHunk": "@@ -113,6 +113,7 @@\n     <spark.bundle.hive.shade.prefix></spark.bundle.hive.shade.prefix>\n     <utilities.bundle.hive.scope>provided</utilities.bundle.hive.scope>\n     <utilities.bundle.hive.shade.prefix></utilities.bundle.hive.shade.prefix>\n+    <argLine>-Xmx1024m -XX:MaxPermSize=256m</argLine>", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDM3NDQ0Mjg3Mg=="}, "originalCommit": {"oid": "2f304675c0c3b6acbe2a1f8b0e6003f93f7eb203"}, "originalPosition": 4}, {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDM3NTU0MzM5MQ==", "bodyText": "Okay, makes sense.\n@vinothchandar I don't see it slowing down, just had a hunch, merging this as this does not seem to have any side-effect.", "url": "https://github.com/apache/hudi/pull/1298#discussion_r375543391", "createdAt": "2020-02-05T22:26:49Z", "author": {"login": "n3nash"}, "path": "pom.xml", "diffHunk": "@@ -113,6 +113,7 @@\n     <spark.bundle.hive.shade.prefix></spark.bundle.hive.shade.prefix>\n     <utilities.bundle.hive.scope>provided</utilities.bundle.hive.scope>\n     <utilities.bundle.hive.shade.prefix></utilities.bundle.hive.shade.prefix>\n+    <argLine>-Xmx1024m -XX:MaxPermSize=256m</argLine>", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDM3NDQ0Mjg3Mg=="}, "originalCommit": {"oid": "2f304675c0c3b6acbe2a1f8b0e6003f93f7eb203"}, "originalPosition": 4}]}}]}}}, "rateLimit": {"limit": 5000, "remaining": 31, "cost": 1, "resetAt": "2021-11-11T21:28:48Z"}}}